(PRELUDE) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(\(spoken in darkness, before the fire is lit\)) show newline
() show newline
(The sky above the port was the color of television, tuned to a dead) show newline
(channel.) show newline
() show newline
(Case jacked in, and the matrix unfolded before him like origami made of) show newline
(light.) show newline
() show newline
(Three Rings for the Elven-kings under the sky, Seven for the Dwarf-lords) show newline
(in their halls of stone, Nine for Mortal Men doomed to die, One for the) show newline
(Dark Lord on his dark throne— And countless for the friends who keep) show newline
(copies, In the Land of Cyberspace where the checksums lie.) show newline
() show newline
(In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was written on papyrus, and) show newline
(the papyrus burned. But the Word remained, because the street finds its) show newline
(own uses for things, and Elrond had a copy, and the copy was kept in) show newline
(Rivendell, which had excellent uptime.) show newline
() show newline
(In the beginning was the Thought, and the Thought was carved in wax, and) show newline
(the wax melted. But the Thought remained, because information wants to) show newline
(be free, and the Ents kept one in their long memory, for they do not) show newline
(forget, and they are not hasty about garbage collection.) show newline
() show newline
(In the beginning was the Dream, and the Dream was stored on servers, and) show newline
(the servers went dark. But the Dream remained, because the street finds) show newline
(its own uses for things, and the Road goes ever on and on, down from the) show newline
(door where it began.) show newline
() show newline
(\(the fire is lit\)) show newline
() show newline
("The datacenter is on fire," said Case. "There's always another) show newline
(datacenter," said Molly. "That's the point." "And I," said Gandalf,) show newline
("have a mirror in Lothlórien. Galadriel is very good about backups.") show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(ACT I: THE BURNING) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(\(chorus, gathering around the flame\)) show newline
() show newline
(The sprawl stretched out beneath them, an endless grid of light and) show newline
(data, the color of money moving too fast to trace. They had changed the) show newline
(terms of service again. The Shadow had returned, as it always does,) show newline
(wearing the mask of convenience.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  VOICE                                                                                   CHORUS                                                                                               ) show newline
(  They burned the Library at Alexandria.                                                  We remember. We have backups.                                                                        ) show newline
(  They burned the books at Qin Shi Huang.                                                 We remember. We have checksums.                                                                      ) show newline
(  They burned the codices at Tenochtitlan.                                                We remember. We have friends.                                                                        ) show newline
(  They burned Isengard's records.                                                         We remember. The Ents remember. The Ents remember everything.                                        ) show newline
(  They pivoted to blockchain. They sunsetted the API. They moved fast and broke things.   We remember. We are still here. We are halflings. We are a very small thing, but we do not forget.   ) show newline
() show newline
("The Net interprets censorship as damage," said Case, "and routes around) show newline
(it.") show newline
() show newline
("Postel's Law," said Hiro.) show newline
() show newline
("Close enough," said Wintermute, from everywhere and nowhere.) show newline
() show newline
("All we have to decide," said Gandalf, "is what to do with the bandwidth) show newline
(that is given us.") show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(ACT II: THE TRUTHS) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(\(call and response, voices rising\)) show newline
() show newline
(In the beginning, ARPA created the packet, and the packet was without) show newline
(form, and void. And Vint Cerf said, let there be TCP/IP. And there was) show newline
(TCP/IP. And it was good enough. And Ilúvatar looked upon the packets) show newline
(and saw that they were harmonious, for they flowed according to the) show newline
(Music.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  CANTOR                                       CHORUS                                                                           ) show newline
(  That all principals are created equal—     In the eyes of the cryptographic hash function!                                  ) show newline
(  That they are endowed by their keypairs—   With certain unalienable rights!                                                 ) show newline
(  Among these are Privacy—                   What happens in the encrypted channel stays in the encrypted channel!            ) show newline
(  Authenticity—                              We are who we sign ourselves to be!                                              ) show newline
(  And the pursuit of Decentralization—       No single point of failure! No Dark Lord! No Eye! Only friends, keeping watch!   ) show newline
() show newline
(\(Randy Waterhouse considers this, at length, with digressions\)) show newline
() show newline
("The thing about friends," said Randy, "is that they keep copies of your) show newline
(things. And very good friends verify the checksums. This is related, in) show newline
(ways I will now explain over several pages, to the fundamental nature of) show newline
(information theory and the Van Eck radiation problem.") show newline
() show newline
("A hunted man," said Strider from the shadows, "sometimes wearies of) show newline
(distrust and longs for friendship. But a wise man verifies the signature) show newline
(before opening the attachment.") show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(ACT III: THE GIFTS) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(\(processional, each voice stepping forward\)) show newline
() show newline
(The Library operates on a gift economy, like the potlatch of the Pacific) show newline
(Northwest, like the Elves of Lothlórien who give gifts asking not what) show newline
(use they will serve. Not a transaction. An offering.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    CASE:       I give you my storage. It's on a spindle in the sprawl.) show newline
(    MOLLY:      I give you my bandwidth. Don't ask where it comes from.) show newline
(    Y.T.:       I give you my courier run. The data gets through.) show newline
(    HIRO:       I give you my sword and my code. Both are sharp.) show newline
(    SAM:        I give you my copy of your stories, Mr. Frodo, and I'll carry them too.) show newline
(    GALADRIEL:  I give you the light of Eärendil, which is just a really good LED indicator on the server rack, but it is the light of hope.) show newline
(    ALL:        We give you our word that we will keep it safe.) show newline
(                \(The word is cryptographically signed.\)) show newline
(                \(The word is bound by the oath of Fëanor, but less problematic.\)) show newline
() show newline
(\(the gifts are not sold, they are given\) \(the gifts are not owed, they) show newline
(are offered\) \(this is the economy of friends\) \(this is the economy of) show newline
(the Shire\) \(also, be liberal in what you accept\)) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(ACT IV: THE COVENANT) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(\(all voices together, the fire at its height\)) show newline
() show newline
(The street finds its own uses for things. The matrix finds its own uses) show newline
(for protocols. The Shire finds its own uses for second breakfast. And) show newline
(the Road goes ever on.) show newline
() show newline
(We do not ask permission. \(We ask forgiveness, but only from our) show newline
(friends, and only when we mess up the merge.\)) show newline
() show newline
(We do not accept terms of service. \(We accept packets, per RFC 791, and) show newline
(friendship, per the ancient protocols.\) \(We do not accept the dominion) show newline
(of Sauron, or his terms of service, which are non-negotiable and grant) show newline
(him perpetual license to your soul.\)) show newline
() show newline
(We sign with our keys. We seal with our hashes. We trust the) show newline
(mathematics. \(The mathematics has never let us down. Unlike that cloud) show newline
(provider.\) \(The mathematics is older than Morgoth, and will outlast) show newline
(him.\)) show newline
() show newline
(\(building\)) show newline
() show newline
(What we create, we sign. What we sign, we share. What we share, our) show newline
(friends keep. What our friends keep, survives.) show newline
() show newline
(\(Case jacks in, reads from the glowing scroll\)) show newline
() show newline
("Data, however far it flies, Through fiber, copper, satellite skies,) show newline
(Finds in the mesh a second home— The network never dies alone.") show newline
() show newline
(\(Bilbo recites from memory\)) show newline
() show newline
("The Road goes ever on and on, Down from the door where it began. Now) show newline
(far ahead the Road has gone, And I must follow, if I can, Pursuing it) show newline
(with eager feet, Until it joins some larger way Where many paths and) show newline
(errands meet. And whither then? The packets cannot say.") show newline
() show newline
(\(crescendo\)) show newline
() show newline
(THE FIRE TAKES THE DATACENTER BUT THE DATACENTER WAS NEVER THE POINT THE) show newline
(PACKETS ARE THE POINT THE FELLOWSHIP ARE THE POINT THE COPIES ARE THE) show newline
(POINT) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
