(FINALE: THE DAWN) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(\(the fire dies to embers, the sun rises over the Sprawl, and over the) show newline
(Shire, and over all the lands of Middle-earth and Cyberspace\)) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  CASE                                                                                                                MOLLY                                                      ) show newline
(  In the matrix, everything burns. The servers burn. The platforms burn. The business models burn.                    But the data doesn't burn. Not if you're smart about it.   ) show newline
(  We scatter to the ten directions. We carry the keys in our pockets. We carry each other's dreams in our machines.   And when they ask where the library is?                    ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  FRODO                                                 SAM                                                   ) show newline
(  I will take the data, though I do not know the way.   And I'll come with you, Mr. Frodo. I made a backup.   ) show newline
() show newline
(ALL: \(pointing to each other\)) show newline
() show newline
("Here," said Case, jacking out. "And here," said Molly, mirrored eyes) show newline
(reflecting the ember-light. "And here," said Hiro, in the Metaverse and) show newline
(the Shire at once. "And here," said Sam, "in the Shire, where it's) show newline
(safe." "And here," said Elrond, "in Rivendell, until the ships sail.") show newline
() show newline
(Everywhere we are, the library is. We are the library. We are the ones) show newline
(who remember. We are cowboys and halflings and hackers and friends. Even) show newline
(the smallest packet can change the course of the future.) show newline
() show newline
(\(the embers glow\) \(the friends embrace\) \(the packets route\) \(the) show newline
(checksums verify\) \(the eagles come, but only for disaster recovery\)) show newline
() show newline
